<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0" Background="#1E1F22" FontFamily="Segoe UI" FontSize="14" PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">Exporting</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">How to export a completed custom texture world into the Urban Chaos game directory.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Exporting a Custom World</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Once your custom world is complete, use <Bold>Export World</Bold> to write the finished texture world into your Urban Chaos game directory.</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>A finished world should usually have populated texture slots, defined style recipes, configured texture properties, assigned footstep sounds, and a sky image where needed.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/exporting_overview.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">What Gets Exported</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Exporting writes the current custom world project into the correct world folder for use by the game and the Map Editor.</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Texture cells such as <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">tex000</Run> through <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">tex255</Run>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>The world’s <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">Style.TMA</Run> file.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Texture property data such as transparency, masking, illumination, wrapping, and fadeout settings.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Footstep sound mappings for each texture tile.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>The sky image, commonly exported as <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">sky.tga</Run>, if one has been added.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/exporting_export_contents.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Using the Export World Button</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Press the <Bold>Export World</Bold> button in the quick actions bar, or use <Bold>File → Export Finished Custom World to Game</Bold>.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/exporting_export_world_button.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Selecting the Game Textures Directory</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>After pressing <Bold>Export World</Bold>, select the main <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">textures</Run> directory for your Urban Chaos installation.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/exporting_select_textures_directory.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph>For example, on a GOG installation this may look similar to:</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Border Background="#25272B" BorderBrush="#444" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="10"><TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0E0E0" FontFamily="Consolas">C:\Program Files (x86)\GOG Galaxy\Games\Urban Chaos\server\textures\</TextBlock></Border></BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8"><Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12"><TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0"><Run FontWeight="Bold">Note:</Run><Run> Select the main textures directory only. Do not manually select or create a specific world-number folder. The Style Editor uses the current custom world number automatically.</Run></TextBlock></Border></BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">World Number Handling</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>The export process automatically uses the world number assigned when the custom texture set was created. You do not need to type the world number during export.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/exporting_world_number_automatic.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Completing the Export</Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>Confirm the folder selection. The Style Editor writes the custom world files into the game directory. After export, the custom world can be used by the Map Editor and the game, depending on how the map and world number are configured.</Paragraph>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8"><Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosStyleEditor;component/Help/Images/exporting_complete_status.png" MaxWidth="700" Stretch="Uniform"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8"><Border Background="#3A2A2A" BorderBrush="#7A4A4A" BorderThickness="1" CornerRadius="4" Padding="12"><TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0A0A0"><Run FontWeight="Bold">⚠ Important:</Run><Run> Exporting can overwrite files in the target custom world folder. Make sure you are exporting the intended custom world and keep backups before replacing game directory files.</Run></TextBlock></Border></BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer><Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/></BlockUIContainer>
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF">Basic Export Workflow</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0" Foreground="#E0E0E0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Finish importing and editing texture slots.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Configure texture properties and footstep sounds.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Define or update the <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">Style.TMA</Run> recipes.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Add a sky image if the world requires one.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Press <Bold>Export World</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Select the game’s main <Run FontFamily="Consolas" Foreground="#E8B84B">server\textures\</Run> directory.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the export and wait for the editor to complete the operation.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>
</FlowDocument>
